column1: #Text=This directory contains two datasets that are used in the downstream tasks for
#Text=[UIBert: Learning Generic Multimodal Representations for UI Understanding](https://arxiv.org/abs/2107.13731):
#Text=app similar UI component retrieval data (AppSim) and referring expression
#Text=Both datasets are extended from the public Rico dataset, which contains 72k
#Text=They add two different types of annotations to these UIs:
#Text=In AppSim, each datapoint contains two UIs of similar category and the
#Text=    annotation of two semantically similar UI elements on them, such as a “Menu”
#Text=    buttons that appear on two UIs.
#Text=In RefExp, each datapoint contains a UI and a referring expression of a UI
#Text=    element on it, such as “Red button on the top”.
#Text=We use unique image ids in both datasets to represent the UI and they can be
#Text=used to retrieve the original UI data in
#Text=Both data are saved as TFRecords, which makes it easy to be loaded in
#Text=AppSim: Each TFRecord contains unique image ids of an anchor UI and a search
#Text=The anchor UI has one anchor UI element and the search UI has 10 UI
#Text=    elements, one of which is semantically similar to the anchor UI element.
#Text=Bounding box of the anchor UIelement on the anchor UI
#Text=        candidate UI elements on the search UI.
#Text=        similar to the anchor UI element of the anchor UI.
#Text=        UI element in the search UI candidates list.
#Text=RefExp: Each TFRecord has the following features.
#Text=    `image/view_hierarchy` are information extracted from UI’s view hierarchy
#Text=Index of the UI element that is
#Text=        referred to by the referring expression in the `image/object/bbox/…`
#Text=The number of elements is denoted in
#Text=Bounding boxes of leaf nodes in the view hierarchy
#Text=If you use or discuss this dataset in your work, please cite our paper:
#Text=      title={UIBert: Learning Generic Multimodal Representations for UI Understanding},
#Text=      author={Chongyang Bai and Xiaoxue Zang and Ying Xu and Srinivas Sunkara and Abhinav Rastogi and Jindong Chen and Blaise Aguera y Arcas},
